			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Datacratic is hiring a Product Sales Manager with an in depth knowledge of digital marketing across multiple channels including display advertising, email, social, mobile, search and others.&nbsp; The successful candidate will be responsible for taking over and managing an existing pipeline of sales opportunities and will be expected to add to and expand the pipeline. This role has a global focus with clients and prospects in North America, Europe, APAC and Latin America. This is a client-facing position requiring a strong understanding and passion for how data is impacting and changing the digital marketing and ecommerce ecosystem, including experience with real-time programmatic media buying (RTB), machine learning software and concepts associated with predictive modeling, artificial intelligence.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
The role requires an individual who is highly technical and has a foundational understanding of software engineering and complex software systems. A key requirement is an in depth knowledge of the extremely complex digital advertising ecosystem as well as an established network of sr level contacts within that ecosystem.</p>
<p>
The role will report directly to the Head of Sales (currently the CEO) as an individual contributor and also has the capacity to grow into a managerial position at the head of a team.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>What we&rsquo;re looking for:</strong></p>
<p>
Our ideal candidate would be based in New York and requires 4-6 years of digital marketing experience with a preference for performance based marketing. An educational background in mathematics, computer science, statistics, economics or equivalent is a strong plus.</p>
<p>
We are looking for someone with:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Enterprise software sales experience.</li>
<li>
Razor sharp analytical skills and the ability to effectively communicate with both technical and business leaders within our client&rsquo;s organizations.</li>
<li>
Experience with long sales cycles and the ability to effectively manage an extremely large client pipeline.</li>
<li>
An in depth knowledge and understanding of the technical guts of the digital advertising and ecommerce ecosystem.</li>
<li>
The ability to function effectively in a startup environment and to develop ad hoc business processes on the fly.</li>
<li>
A long term love affair with Sales Force Dot Com.</li>
<li>
Strong written and verbal presentation skills and the desire to function as an evangelist for the company at conferences, events and in social media.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>About the job:</strong></p>
<p>
This position will require:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Frequent travel within North America and Europe.</li>
<li>
Accurate forecasting of pipeline opportunities and client revenue.</li>
<li>
Achievement of individual sales and revenue targets.</li>
</ul>
<p>
In this role you will be providing strategic consulting to clients on the use of Datacratic&rsquo;s products.&nbsp; Internally, you will work closely with Product Management to create a regular feedback loop that aligns client&rsquo;s needs and requirements with the product roadmap.&nbsp; You will be supported by a world class data science team and act as the bridge between them and the client.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ll be expected to manage client relationships, contracts, and invoicing.</p>
<p>
<strong>What we offer:</strong></p>
<p>
Datacratic provides a challenging and creative environment where personal initiative, accountability and collaboration are encouraged.&nbsp; We are committed to learning and mentoring.&nbsp; Our work style is agile but in a pragmatic, non-dogmatic way, embracing challenging new ideas and innovation.&nbsp; We have a bilingual work environment (French and English) and customers who speak both languages.&nbsp; Being functionally bilingual will be a big advantage.</p>
<p>
We care deeply about maintaining a healthy and rewarding work environment.&nbsp; Datacratic offers a competitive salary; four weeks paid vacation, a robust Group insurance plan, and a Wellness program. &nbsp;We want people to own the results of their work, so we offer stock options.&nbsp; Best of all, we are head-quartered in downtown Montr&eacute;al with a second office in New York City, two of the coolest cities in the world in which to work &hellip;and play.</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>About Datacratic:</strong></p>
<p>
Datacratic is a machine learning and predictive modeling company.&nbsp; We solve complex challenges with data.&nbsp; The team is made up of business people, engineers, programmers and scientists all working together and pushing the limits of what a machine can do in both memory size and processing capacity.&nbsp; Datacratic provides optimization for Data Management Platforms (DMPs), Demand Side Platforms (DSPs), Agency Trading Desks (ATDs), E-Commerce Web Sites and others in the real-time marketing ecosystem.&nbsp; Originally founded as Recoset in February 2010 and headquartered in Montr&eacute;al, Datacratic is privately held with backing from Real Ventures and BDC Venture Capital. For more information visit datacratic.com.</p>
