			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Datacratic is hiring an Integration Developer for our Integration Engineering team based in NYC. This team is responsible for designing and implementing solutions connecting our machine-learning and real-time optimization products with customer systems, so they can benefit from our unique technology.&nbsp; If you get excited about integrating complex systems to solve customer problems and drive our growth and success, then this job is for you.</p>
<p>
<strong>What we&#39;re looking for:</strong></p>
<p>
We are looking for generalist software developers to work on the productization of our applications: creating and standardizing systems and processes for configuration, deployment, testing, monitoring and deployment to AWS, as well as working with our clients to adapt our technology to their needs and develop new features as appropriate. Our product and technology teams are not segregated, so you would also be exposed to the core technology and be expected to dive down into it as necessary.</p>
<p>
<strong>About the Job:</strong></p>
<p>
This is a customer-facing engineering role.&nbsp; You should be excited about the prospect of meeting with customers to understand their needs, communicating the benefits and attributes of our software products, designing solutions to meet their needs, and contributing to the evolution of our platform and products based on that experience.</p>
<p>
Beyond that, we hire primarily for team fit and general technical excellence, so we don&#39;t have a hard list of &ldquo;you must know X.&rdquo; We are looking for someone with 0-5 years of paid software development experience under their belt, with pay commensurate with experience.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Here is a list of the technologies we currently use; if you have experience with a few of these or something equivalent, and would be excited about learning the rest, we want to hear from you:</p>
<ul>
<li>
NodeJS/V8: server-side Javascript that can easily call into compiled code...</li>
<li>
Python: ...for when NodeJS&#39;s asynchronous world-view just doesn&#39;t cut it...</li>
<li>
Coffeescript: ...for when you want your Javascript to look more like Python</li>
<li>
C++ 11: for when things needs to go fast</li>
<li>
Amazon Web Services/StarCluster: cloud deployment</li>
<li>
RESTful API&#39;s: our preference and the standard in the industries we work in currently</li>
<li>
Protovis/D3: for when you want to make pre tty pictures of your data</li>
<li>
R/SciPy/Mathematica: for when you just want to crunch some numbers</li>
<li>
Experience or expertise in any aspect of data science is a plus: machine learning, data analysis, visualization, statistics, advanced maths etc.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>What we offer:</strong></p>
<p>
Datacratic provides a challenging and creative environment where personal initiative, accountability and collaboration are encouraged. We are committed to learning and mentoring.&nbsp; Our work style is agile but in a pragmatic, non-dogmatic way; embracing challenging new ideas and innovation.&nbsp; We have a bilingual work environment (French and English). Fluent bilingualism is not a requirement; however a willingness to learn is required.</p>
<p>
We care deeply about maintaining a healthy and rewarding work environment.&nbsp; Datacratic offers a competitive salary; four weeks paid vacation, a robust Group insurance plan and a Wellness program. We want people to own the results of their work, so we offer stock options.</p>
<p>
<strong>Datacratic:</strong></p>
<p>
Datacratic is a machine learning and predictive modeling company focused on solving complex challenges with big data. The team is made up of engineers, programmers and scientists all working together and pushing the limits of what a machine can do in both memory size and processing capacity.&nbsp; Datacratic provides optimization for Data Management Platforms (DMPs), Demand Side Platforms (DSPs), Agency Trading Desks (ATDs), E-Commerce Web Sites and others in the real-time marketing ecosystem. Originally founded as Recoset in February 2010 and headquartered in Montr&eacute;al, Datacratic is privately held with backing from Real Ventures and BDC Venture Capital. For more information visit Datacratic.com.</p>
